# Documentation sync on fundamental changes

When you change something **fundamental**, update the relevant documentation **in the same task** before finishing.

## What counts as fundamental

- **Scripts:** `pnpm dev`, `build`, `lint`, `preview`
- **Data model:** Dexie schema, types in `src/models/types.ts`, migrations
- **Features:** new views, export/import format, routing
- **Stack:** dependencies, build config, path aliases

Cosmetic refactors and internal renames with no user-visible effect are **not** fundamental unless docs name the old symbol.

## Where to update

| Change type | Update at minimum |
|-------------|-------------------|
| Run commands / setup | [README.md](../../README.md) |
| Data model / IndexedDB | README + inline comments in `src/db/schema.ts` if non-obvious |
| Cursor rules/skills | [.cursor/README.md](../README.md) — `projocalypse-<topic>.mdc` / `projocalypse-<topic>/` naming per **`projocalypse-filenames.mdc`** |

## Quality bar

- Replace **stale commands** wherever they appear in docs you touch.
- Keep edits **scoped** to what changed; no unrelated doc drive-bys.
